title: Grateful Dead Live at Academy of Music on 1972-03-27
description: Bertha, Black Throated Wind, Chinatown Shuffle, Brown Eyed Women, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Me And Bobby McGee, Mr. Charlie, Looks Like Rain, Deal, It Hurts Me Too, Cumberland Blues, Playin' In The Band Greatest Story Ever Told, Ramble On Rose, Big Boss Man, El Paso, Good Lovin', Me & My Uncle, Two Souls In Communion, Sugar Magnolia, Loser, Casey Jones, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: Great Show This show is a good example of the Grateful Dead in 1972...excellent.  I especially like "Loser" from this show.  Download it.
Sound quality Have had a brief listen to this, the sound quality is, er, dodgy!

Collection/sentimental value only don't get this show if you are looking for quality. low vocals and grainy sound. if you are looking to fill the gaps in your collection, pick this show up, but this is for tolerant ears only....audience is high in mix and the music itself is very difficult to listen to

1st Dead show........ This was my very first GD show.  I had gone to ticketron with Greg & David to get myself a John Sebastian ticket,  and they were getting Dead tickets.  The LST began because John Sebastian was sold out.  G & D convinced me to get a dead ticket.   All I knew was Casey Jones, so Greg told me to yell for Bertha.  We sat in the balcony,  and what I remember most was the Casey Jones went on forever......And the Hell's Angels were beating people up outside before the show started.  Some people said to make good for that they threw out bags of opium into the crowd prior to the show....
